---
import PortalLayout from "../layouts/PortalLayout.astro";
---

<PortalLayout title="Playbook" mainBg="#f0f9ff">
  <div class="max-w-4xl">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-2">Playbook</h1>
    <p class="text-stone-600 mb-8">Architecture, workflows, and standards for every site we build</p>

    <div class="space-y-8">

      <!-- Full Stack -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">Full Stack</h2>
        <ol class="space-y-3">
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">1.</span>
            <div><strong>Astro + Tailwind CSS</strong> — pages and styling</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">2.</span>
            <div><strong>GitHub (<a href="https://github.com/Spirit-Media-US" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">Spirit-Media-US</a>)</strong> — code only, never media</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">3.</span>
            <div><strong>Netlify</strong> — hosting, auto-deploys on push to <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">main</code></div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">4.</span>
            <div><strong>Cloudflare</strong> — domain, SSL, CDN, security</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">5.</span>
            <div><strong>Cloudflare R2</strong> — all images, audio, video</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">6.</span>
            <div><strong>Sanity (<a href="https://sanity.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">sanity.io</a>)</strong> — CMS for client content editing and media management with auto-optimization (MCP connected)</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">7.</span>
            <div><strong>GoHighLevel</strong> — CRM &amp; forms for internal sites, tagged by ministry (MCP connected)</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">8.</span>
            <div><strong>Claude (<a href="https://claude.ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">claude.ai</a>)</strong> — conversational updates and builds</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">9.</span>
            <div><strong>UptimeRobot</strong> — uptime monitoring (every 5 min, all sites)</div>
          </li>
        </ol>

        <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-800 mt-6 mb-3">MCP Tools</h3>
        <ol class="space-y-3" start="10">
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">10.</span>
            <div><strong>Stitch</strong> (Google Stitch 2.0) — AI-powered design, generates pages and design systems</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">11.</span>
            <div><strong>Playwright</strong> — browser testing, screenshots, cross-browser QA</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">12.</span>
            <div><strong>Google Docs MCP</strong> — documents, proposals, reports, content drafts</div>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <!-- Website Migration Protocol -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-rose-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-rose-700 mb-1">Website Migration Protocol</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm mb-1">Client-facing name: <strong>The Transformation System</strong> &nbsp;·&nbsp; Pipeline type: <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">migration</code></p>
        <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm mb-5">Nine AI-powered phases. Phase 5 (CAR) is the hard gate — nothing past it until approved. Every migration follows this map, no exceptions.</p>

        <div class="space-y-4">

          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-rose-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">1</div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800 text-sm">Infrastructure</p>
              <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">GitHub repo, Netlify site, Sanity project, Cloudflare domain, R2 bucket. <strong class="text-stone-700">Create <code class="bg-white px-1 rounded">CLAUDE.md</code> in repo root before any other work.</strong> Dashboard card created in registry.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-rose-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">2</div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800 text-sm">Content Extraction</p>
              <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">Claude crawls all pages of the original live site. Saves headings, body text, CTAs, nav structure, footer, images, media. Extracts brand colors, fonts, and logo from the site's CSS/assets.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-rose-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">3</div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800 text-sm">Build All Pages (Rough)</p>
              <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">Claude builds every page from extracted content — structure and copy only. Wires typography and brand colors into <code class="bg-white px-1 rounded">global.css</code> from Phase 2 extraction. No design polish — faithful content migration first.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-rose-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">4</div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800 text-sm">Wire Sanity CMS</p>
              <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">Define schemas. Migrate all hardcoded content into Sanity documents. Wire Astro pages to Sanity. Deploy schema to cloud. Set up Sanity &rarr; Netlify deploy webhook.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Phase 5 — CAR Gate -->
          <div class="border border-rose-300 bg-rose-50 rounded-lg p-4 my-2">
            <p class="font-bold text-rose-700 text-sm mb-2">Phase 5 — CAR / Transformation Layer Report (THE GATE)</p>
            <p class="text-stone-600 text-xs mb-3">Nothing from Phase 6 forward happens until the CAR is reviewed and critical fixes are approved. This prevents polishing a site that has structural problems.</p>
            <div class="space-y-2">
              <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">Claude runs all automated scans + Migration Fidelity scan (compares original site against new build). Generates Transformation Layer Report (Google Doc):</p>
              <ul class="text-stone-500 text-xs space-y-1 ml-3">
                <li>&bull; <strong>Part One:</strong> Already Delivered</li>
                <li>&bull; <strong>Part Two:</strong> Critical Fixes (must fix)</li>
                <li>&bull; <strong>Part Three:</strong> Recommended Improvements (optional)</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="text-stone-600 text-xs font-semibold pt-1">You review &rarr; You approve critical fixes &rarr; Claude implements.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-rose-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">6</div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800 text-sm">Design Refinement (Stitch)</p>
              <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">Claude uses Stitch MCP to generate improved page designs based on extracted brand. This is where the site goes from "faithful migration" to "better than the original." Playwright screenshots for your review.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-rose-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">7</div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800 text-sm">QA</p>
              <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">Claude runs Pre-Launch QA, Post-Launch QA (Lighthouse, SEO, accessibility), content-diff against original site, cross-browser testing via Playwright. Fixes everything found — iterates until all scans pass.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-rose-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">8</div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800 text-sm">Launch</p>
              <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">Claude connects custom domain, confirms SSL, submits sitemap to GSC, sets up UptimeRobot, enables GA4, wires Sanity &rarr; Netlify webhook. Verifies everything is live.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-rose-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">9</div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800 text-sm">Client Delivery &amp; Roadmap</p>
              <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs mb-2">Claude generates delivery email + post-launch roadmap (Google Doc). Kevin sends the email.</p>
              <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs mb-1 font-semibold">Email template:</p>
              <div class="relative">
                <div class="bg-stone-100 px-3 py-2 rounded text-xs text-stone-600 whitespace-pre-wrap leading-relaxed" id="delivery-email">Subject: Your website is live! — [Site Name]

Hi [Client Name],

Your new website is live at [domain]!

We've put together a guide to help you manage your site content on your own:
→ https://portal.spiritmediapublishing.com/clients

To set up your team's content editing access, please reply with the name and email address for each person who should be able to edit. We'll send them a Sanity Studio invite with everything they need to get started.

For anything beyond content edits — new pages, design changes, forms, or technical work — just email us at hello@spiritmediapublishing.com.

Welcome aboard!
SMP Team</div>
                <button class="copy-btn absolute top-2 right-2 px-3 py-1 bg-rose-50 hover:bg-rose-100 text-rose-700 rounded text-xs font-semibold font-sans" data-copy-target="delivery-email">Copy</button>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>

        <!-- Tools link -->
        <div class="mt-6 pt-5 border-t border-stone-200">
          <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm">Automated tools for this pipeline: <a href="/pipelines" class="text-rose-700 hover:underline font-semibold">Pipelines &rarr; Website Migration</a></p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- New Site Build Protocol -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-teal-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-teal-700 mb-1">SMP Build Protocol (New Sites)</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm mb-1">Pipeline type: <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">newsite</code></p>
        <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm mb-5">Nine AI-powered phases for building a brand new website from scratch. Phase 5 (CAR) is the hard gate. No existing site to migrate — content and design are created fresh.</p>

        <div class="space-y-4">

          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-teal-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">1</div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800 text-sm">Discovery &amp; Brand</p>
              <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">Claude crawls the client's social media, Google Business profile, and any web presence. Extracts brand voice, colors, fonts, audience signals. Generates creative brief + sitemap recommendation (Google Doc). You review and approve.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-teal-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">2</div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800 text-sm">Infrastructure</p>
              <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">GitHub repo, Netlify site, Sanity project, Cloudflare domain, R2 bucket, <code class="bg-white px-1 rounded">CLAUDE.md</code>. Dashboard card created in registry. Same bootstrap tool as migration.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-teal-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">3</div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800 text-sm">Design System (Stitch)</p>
              <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">Claude uses Stitch MCP to generate full page designs from the brand reference. Auto-creates design system (colors, typography, components). Exports <code class="bg-white px-1 rounded">design.md</code>. Wires design tokens into <code class="bg-white px-1 rounded">global.css</code> — palette and typography locked before any page CSS.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-teal-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">4</div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800 text-sm">Build Pages + Content + Sanity</p>
              <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">Claude builds every page in Astro + Tailwind from the design system. Adds all copy, SEO meta, JSON-LD. Defines Sanity schemas, migrates content into CMS, wires pages to fetch from Sanity, deploys schema, sets up webhook. Full site — rough but complete.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Phase 5 — CAR Gate -->
          <div class="border border-teal-300 bg-teal-50 rounded-lg p-4 my-2">
            <p class="font-bold text-teal-700 text-sm mb-2">Phase 5 — CAR / Review Gate (THE GATE)</p>
            <p class="text-stone-600 text-xs mb-3">Nothing from Phase 6 forward happens until the CAR is reviewed and critical fixes are approved. This prevents polishing a site that has structural problems.</p>
            <div class="space-y-2">
              <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">Claude runs all automated scans. Generates Transformation Layer Report (Google Doc):</p>
              <ul class="text-stone-500 text-xs space-y-1 ml-3">
                <li>&bull; <strong>Part One:</strong> Already Delivered</li>
                <li>&bull; <strong>Part Two:</strong> Critical Fixes (must fix)</li>
                <li>&bull; <strong>Part Three:</strong> Recommended Improvements (optional)</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="text-stone-600 text-xs font-semibold pt-1">You review &rarr; You approve critical fixes &rarr; Claude implements.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-teal-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">6</div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800 text-sm">Design Polish (Stitch)</p>
              <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">After CAR approval, Claude uses Stitch MCP to generate refined designs based on CAR feedback. Refines spacing, responsiveness, micro-interactions. Playwright screenshots for your review.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-teal-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">7</div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800 text-sm">QA</p>
              <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">Claude runs Pre-Launch QA, Post-Launch QA (Lighthouse, SEO, accessibility, mobile), cross-browser testing via Playwright, form testing end-to-end. Fixes everything found — iterates until all scans pass.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-teal-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">8</div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800 text-sm">Launch</p>
              <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">Claude connects custom domain, confirms SSL, submits sitemap to GSC, sets up UptimeRobot, enables GA4, wires Sanity &rarr; Netlify webhook. Verifies everything is live.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-teal-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">9</div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800 text-sm">Client Delivery &amp; Roadmap</p>
              <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">Claude generates delivery email + post-launch roadmap (Google Doc) with recommended improvements not included in initial build. Kevin sends the email.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>

        <!-- Tools link -->
        <div class="mt-6 pt-5 border-t border-stone-200">
          <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm">Automated tools for this pipeline: <a href="/pipelines" class="text-teal-700 hover:underline font-semibold">Pipelines &rarr; New Site Build</a></p>
        </div>

        <!-- Design Library link -->
        <div class="mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-stone-200">
          <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm">Use the <a href="/design-library" class="text-teal-700 hover:underline font-semibold">Design Library &rarr;</a> to browse all 7 style packages and 21 color palettes. When starting a new site, select a package and tell Claude which one to use.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Stitch — AI Design Tool -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-2">Stitch — AI Design Tool</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm mb-4"><strong>Google Stitch 2.0</strong> is an AI-powered design tool available as an MCP server on Bethel. It is the standard SMP workflow for all new site builds, major redesigns, and new page layouts.</p>

        <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-800 mb-2">When to Use Stitch</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-1 text-stone-600 text-sm mb-4">
          <li>&bull; New site builds (Phase 3 — Design &amp; Content)</li>
          <li>&bull; Major redesigns of existing sites</li>
          <li>&bull; New page layouts or landing pages</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-800 mb-2">4-Step Design Workflow</h3>
        <div class="space-y-3 mb-4">
          <div class="bg-stone-50 border-l-4 border-red-700 px-4 py-3 rounded-r">
            <p class="font-semibold text-stone-700 text-sm mb-1">1. Capture a style reference</p>
            <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">Screenshot or paste a URL into Stitch as the visual starting point.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-stone-50 border-l-4 border-red-700 px-4 py-3 rounded-r">
            <p class="font-semibold text-stone-700 text-sm mb-1">2. Stitch generates a full page design</p>
            <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">Stitch creates the design and auto-generates a design system (colors, typography, component rules).</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-stone-50 border-l-4 border-red-700 px-4 py-3 rounded-r">
            <p class="font-semibold text-stone-700 text-sm mb-1">3. Export design.md</p>
            <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">Stitch outputs a <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">design.md</code> file — keep it in the project root for reference.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-stone-50 border-l-4 border-red-700 px-4 py-3 rounded-r">
            <p class="font-semibold text-stone-700 text-sm mb-1">4. Claude Code implements in Astro/Tailwind</p>
            <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">Hand the design.md to Claude Code. It builds the pages in Astro + Tailwind CSS to match the Stitch design.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-800 mb-2">Setup</h3>
        <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm mb-2">Stitch is available in <strong>every site directory</strong> automatically via a <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">.mcp.json</code> symlink. No setup needed — just start using the <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">mcp__stitch__</code> tools in Claude Code.</p>
        <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded p-3 text-sm text-amber-800">
          Use <strong>Gemini 3.1 Pro</strong> in Stitch — not 3.0 Flash. This is set in the MCP config.
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Media -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-2">Media</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm mb-4">Media never goes in GitHub. All repos block this via .gitignore.</p>
        <div class="space-y-2 text-stone-600 text-sm mb-4">
          <p><strong>Images:</strong> Managed through <strong>Sanity</strong> — clients upload directly in Sanity Studio. Auto-optimized and served via Sanity CDN. No SMP involvement needed.</p>
          <p><strong>Audio:</strong> Stored in <strong>Cloudflare R2</strong> — Kevin uploads manually.</p>
          <p><strong>Video:</strong> Hosted on <strong>YouTube</strong> and embedded on site (adds SEO value). R2 as backup when YouTube isn't appropriate.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded p-3 text-sm text-amber-800 mb-4">
          ⚠️ <strong>Never rename or delete a live R2 file</strong> — it will break every page that references it. (Sanity handles its own references safely.)
        </div>

        <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-800 mb-2">R2 Bucket &amp; Custom Domain</h3>
        <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm mb-2">One bucket organized by site, served from a clean subdomain:</p>
        <div class="bg-stone-100 px-4 py-2 rounded font-mono text-xs text-stone-600 mb-2">assets.spiritmediapublishing.com</div>
        <div class="bg-stone-100 px-4 py-3 rounded font-mono text-xs text-stone-600 mb-4 whitespace-pre leading-relaxed">spirit-media-assets/
├── spirit-media-publishing/  (videos, audio, pdfs)
├── fathers-heart-bible/      (audio, videos)
├── work-on-yourself/         (audio)
└── believers-library/        (videos)</div>
        <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs mb-4">Shared assets (logos used across sites) go in <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">spirit-media-publishing/</code>. Name files lowercase with hyphens: <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">genesis-chapter-1-audio.mp3</code></p>

        <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-800 mb-2">How to add media to R2 (audio/video)</h3>
        <ol class="space-y-1 text-stone-600 text-sm">
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">1.</span> Client shares Google Drive folder with Kevin</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">2.</span> Kevin downloads and organizes files</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">3.</span> Upload to the correct site folder in R2 at <a href="https://dash.cloudflare.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">dash.cloudflare.com</a></li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">4.</span> File is live immediately at <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">assets.spiritmediapublishing.com/[site]/[file]</code></li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">5.</span> Kevin updates site code to point to the new R2 URL</li>
        </ol>
        <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs mt-3">For images, clients upload directly in Sanity Studio — no R2 or SMP involvement needed.</p>
      </section>

      <!-- Forms & GHL -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-2">Forms &amp; GoHighLevel</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm mb-4">For Spirit Media internal sites, contact forms route to our GoHighLevel CRM, tagged by site. For client sites, forms may use Netlify Forms or another provider depending on the project.</p>

        <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-800 mb-2">GHL Tagging Strategy (Internal Sites)</h3>
        <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm mb-2">Every internal form applies a source tag so contacts can be segmented by ministry:</p>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-4">
          <table class="w-full text-sm text-left border border-stone-200 rounded">
            <thead class="bg-stone-100">
              <tr>
                <th class="px-3 py-2 text-stone-700 font-semibold">Form / Entry Point</th>
                <th class="px-3 py-2 text-stone-700 font-semibold">GHL Tag</th>
                <th class="px-3 py-2 text-stone-700 font-semibold">Pipeline</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="text-stone-600">
